Package seedu.address.commons.core.index

Class Index

  • java.lang.Object
    • seedu.address.commons.core.index.Index
  • public class Index
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a zero-based or one-based index.

    Index should be used right from the start (when parsing in a new user input), so that if the current component wants to communicate with another component, it can send an Index to avoid having to know what base the other component is using for its index. However, after receiving the Index, that component can convert it back to an int if the index will not be passed to a different component again.
